<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/graph-operations> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Core graph algorithms. neighborhood() collects all nodes within N hops using BFS in both directions via the adjacency maps. subgraph() extracts the visible portion — only edges where both endpoints are in the neighborhood. These power the depth slider: depth 1 shows immediate neighbors, depth 99 shows everything." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/graph-operations> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#graph-core> .
