<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/depth-filtering> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The key UX innovation. Instead of showing the entire graph (overwhelming), the viewer shows a neighborhood of configurable depth around the selected node. Depth 1 shows immediate neighbors (~5-10 nodes), depth 2 shows two hops (~15-30), depth 99 shows everything. The BFS algorithm uses forward and backward adjacency maps for O(hop-count) traversal." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/depth-filtering> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#philosophy> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/depth-filtering> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Depth-Based Filtering" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/depth-filtering> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "depth-filtering" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/depth-filtering> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/depth-filtering> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#concept> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/depth-filtering> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/data-driven> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Core principle: the PureScript/JS code contains zero domain-specific knowledge. Every visual element — node kinds, colors, shapes, titles, descriptions — comes from JSON data files. A new knowledge graph on any topic works by providing config.json + graph.json without touching code. This enables the universal viewer and the reusable CI workflow." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/graph-browser/rdf/node/data-driven> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#philosophy> .
